Government of Maharashtra
Department of Law and Justice
Government Decision No: Provisional 2025 / Q. No.81 / Q.12
Fifth Floor, Main Building, Madam Kama Marg,
Martyr Rajguru Chowk, Mantralaya, Mumbai 400 032.
Date: September 22, 2025
Read: - 1) Government Judgment, Law & Justice Department No. Provisional 2024 / P.S. No.81 / Ka.12, D. 27.03.2025.
2) Government Decisions, Finance Department, No. Posts 2016 / P.S. 8/16 APC, D. 26.08.2025.
The Government's Decisions:
Gram Nyayalayas were established in the state under the Gram Nyayalayas Act, 2008.
The posts sanctioned for these Gram Nyayalayas are temporary in nature and belong to the Finance Department.
As per the directions, these posts have been extended from time to time. Read earlier under A.No. 1 here.
A total of 142 temporary posts in 27 Gram Nyayalayas in the state have been created. 01.03.2025त Date 31.08.2025
This period has been extended.
2. For smooth functioning of the aforesaid Gram Nyayalaya, read below under A.No. 2 here:
142 Temporary posts to be extended for a period from date 01.09.2025 to date 28.02.2026
It's coming.
